data.name: XResultSetMetaData
desc: can be used to find out about the types and properties of the columns in a ResultSet.

methods.name: getCatalogName
desc: gets a column's table's catalog name.

methods.name: getColumnCount
desc: returns the number of columns in this ResultSet.

methods.name: getColumnDisplaySize
desc: indicates the column's normal max width in chars.

methods.name: getColumnLabel
desc: gets the suggested column title for use in printouts and displays.

methods.name: getColumnName
desc: gets a column's name.

methods.name: getColumnServiceName
desc: returns the fully-qualified name of the service whose instances are manufactured if the method com.sun.star.sdbc.XResultSet..getObject() is called to retrieve a value from the column.

methods.name: getColumnType
desc: retrieves a column's SQL type.

methods.name: getColumnTypeName
desc: retrieves a column's database-specific type name.

methods.name: getPrecision
desc: gets a column's number of decimal digits.

methods.name: getScale
desc: gets a column's number of digits to right of the decimal point.

methods.name: getSchemaName
desc: gets a column's table's schema.

methods.name: getTableName
desc: gets a column's table name.

methods.name: isAutoIncrement
desc: indicates whether the column is automatically numbered, thus read-only.

methods.name: isCaseSensitive
desc: indicates whether a column's case matters.

methods.name: isCurrency
desc: indicates whether the column is a cash value.

methods.name: isDefinitelyWritable
desc: indicates whether a write on the column will definitely succeed.

methods.name: isNullable
desc: indicates the nullability of values in the designated column.

methods.name: isReadOnly
desc: indicates whether a column is definitely not writable.

methods.name: isSearchable
desc: indicates whether the column can be used in a where clause.

methods.name: isSigned
desc: indicates whether values in the column are signed numbers.

methods.name: isWritable
desc: indicates whether it is possible for a write on the column to succeed.
